@@ -88,6 +88,15 @@
 	not set or the command is not found on the system, pakku will try to guess the
 	command between sudo, doas and su.
 
+*AllowedAurMaintainers =* maintainer ...::
+	A whitelist of approved AUR maintainers. Multiple maintainers are separated
+	by spaces, and the option may be repeated on several lines to accumulate
+	names. When this list is non-empty, pakku will not build or install any
+	AUR package (including dependencies) whose maintainer is missing, empty, or
+	not present in the list. The check is performed before any PKGBUILD or
+	included file is executed, so untrusted packages are never built. If the
+	list is empty or unset (the default), the check is disabled.
+
 See Also
 --------
 linkman:pacman.conf[5], linkman:pakku[8]
